The country has also recorded 88 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Thursday. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in the Eastern Cape. “Regrettably, we report 88 more COVID-19 related deaths: 33 from Eastern Cape, 25 from the Free State, 5 from Gauteng, 2 from KwaZulu-Natal, 5 from Limpopo and 18 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. This brings the total number of deaths to 21 289. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 5 383 078.
